Apt	Aptorian demon native to Shadow and aligned with High House Shadow. Aptorians are described as about nine feet tall with a flat head, a single central eye, a long snout, a long sinuous neck, and a midnight black hairy body with one front leg and two hind legs. Their blood is black, and their coastal villages are raided by Artorallah demons.
Baudin	Companion to Felisin Paran and Heboric after the Cull; described as huge and bestial, with small narrow-set eyes and a thuglike appearance, yet he shows surprising knowledge of the Malazan Empire.
Beneth	Korelri slave in the Otataral mining camp of Skullcup, a large astonishingly handsome man with high cheekbones, long curly black hair groomed with whale oil, thick scarred wrists, clean nails, and deep set eyes. He rose to a crime lord role in the camp and gained the trust of Commandant Sawark.
Blistig	Malazan Commander of the Aren Guard, a burly armed bearded man who wore a torc on his left arm to denote rank. He had a blunt wide face with solid broad features and scarred cheeks, and was known by a mocking nickname used out of his earshot.
Bult	An experienced Wickan warrior serving as second-in-command to Fist Coltaine during the Malazan campaign in Seven Cities. Though Coltaine occasionally referred to him as "uncle," the actual family connection remained ambiguous. A distinctive scar running from the right jawline to the left brow gave his wide face a folded appearance, while his gnarled legs and jagged teeth added to his weathered appearance. Despite his worn features, he maintained a sharp sense of humor, often joking and laughing with his commander and fellow staff.
Coltaine	Leader of the Wickan Crow clan, about forty years old, with a lean lined face, thin wide mouth, and dark deep set eyes marked by squint tracks. He wore oiled braids knotted with crow feather fetishes, a battered chain vest over a hide shirt, and a crow feather cloak, and became the first Wickan Fist after pledging loyalty to the Malazan Empire.
Duiker	Imperial Historian attached to the Malaz 7th Army, born on the plains of Dal Hon, with dark skin and fluent Dosii that served him well in Seven Cities. A veteran soldier skilled with sword and crossbow, he wore local dress including a cowled Telaba cloak while on campaign.
Felisin Paran|Felisin	Youngest Paran sister of house Paran, sister of Ganoes and Tavore, often described as too soft for this world.
Gryllen	A D'ivers known as the Tide of Madness, capable of transforming into a swarm of thousands of rats. He had terrorized the city of Y'Ghatan until Malazans drove him out using fire. Travelling as a wealthy merchant called Nawahl Ebur in a palanquin carried by undead servants, he pursued ascendancy through the Path of Hands in the Raraku desert.
Heboric Light Touch|Heboric	Former High Priest of Fener and an exiled historian, toad-like and bald, his body covered in Fener tattoos and his hands long since severed.
Icarium	Mixed blood Jaghut, a Jhag wanderer who suffers constant amnesia and a fractured mind that recalls fragments of ancient events while forgetting recent days. Known by many names such as Lifestealer and Maker of Time, he travels with his companion Mappo Runt and is famed across the world.
Iskaral Pust|Iskaral|Pust	Old Dal Honese High Priest of Shadow and Magus of High House Shadow who lived in Tesem, an abandoned monastery in Seven Cities. He claimed to be Shadowthrone’s chosen mortal and master of Rashan, Meanas, and Thyr, and was a scrawny tattooed man with a hawk nose, wiry beard, and skin like dark honey.
Kamist Reloe|Kamist|Reloe	High Mage in the Army of the Apocalypse, described as gaunt to the point of skeletal, with grey hair cut to a stubble, a tightly curled iron beard, prominent cheekbones, and sunken eyes. A senior mage figure in the rebellion with a severe and ascetic appearance.
Keneb	Captain in the Orbal garrison on Seven Cities, husband of Selv and father of Kesen and Vaneb, with Minala as his sister in law. An officer of the Malazan Empire whose household ties and garrison role defined his place in the early Seven Cities crisis.
Kimloc	A Tanno Spiritwalker residing in Ehrlitan, distinguished by his role as a spiritual guide and healer within Seven Cities. An elderly man with amber eyes, dressed in an orange robe, whose physical presence conveyed both wisdom and otherworldly connection. His residence was a hidden dwelling within a merchant neighborhood featuring distinctive glass walls and linen-draped doorways. The household bustled with activity, including his granddaughters, medical staff, and military personnel, suggesting his importance as both a family patriarch and community figure. His laughter reportedly sounded like blowing sand, emphasizing his spiritual essence and connection to the desert environment.
Korbolo Dom|Dom	Half Napan Fist in the Malazan Army stationed in Halaf, blue skinned with pudgy hands and thick lips, shaved hairless with dusty blue skin latticed by scars and an expression of cool disdain. A hard edged Malazan officer known for his contempt of gods and magic.
Kulp	Cadre mage in the Malaz 7th Army whose warren is Meanas. Described as squat with a narrow face, white hair, wiry eyebrows, and a sunburned look. A professional soldier mage who serves as a trusted specialist amid the army ranks.
Lady Gaesen|Gaesen	Noblewoman living in Unta and wife of Lord Hilrac, described as a gaunt old woman with a haughty imperious manner.
Leoman of the Flails|Leoman	Captain in the Raraku Apocalypse and bodyguard of Sha'ik, known as Leoman of the Flails. Lean and dark skinned with startling light blue eyes, he carried two one handed morning stars and a crossbow, and wore a colorless Telaba scarf over a peaked iron helm.
List	Young recruit and corporal in Fifth Company of the Malaz 7th Army in Hissar who served under Fist Coltaine. Trained for urban combat and escort missions, he was noted for dying in every mock engagement, which left him lingering near the command tent and listening to strategy sessions.
Lord Hilrac|Hilrac	Nobleman living in Unta and husband of Lady Gaesen, described as a regal older man with a shaved scalp and short grey beard.
Lostara Yil	Pardu woman from Ehrlitan and officer in the Red Blades, holding the rank of captain and serving under Tene Baralta. She was described as dark skinned with Pardu tattoos, large black eyes set wide above high cheekbones, and a narrow aquiline nose.
Mallick Rel|Mallick|Rel	Chief advisor to High Fist Pormqual on Seven Cities and a Falari Jhistal priest of Mael with access to the Warren of Ruse. Described as fat with soft hands, full lips, heavy lidded eyes, and skin the color of oiled leather, with short colorless hair, green stained teeth, and ocean blue robes adorned with rings.
Mappo Runt|Mappo|Runt	Full blooded Trell and companion to Icarium, big even for his people with broad shoulders, sinewy long arms, and a mane of black hair braided and studded with fetishes. He had deep warm brown skin, sand colored eyes in a robust face, massive sharp canines, and could see in the dark.
Mebra	A Seven Cities spy in Ehrlitan, who secretly hated the Malazan occupation of his home continent. He exemplified deception and untrustworthiness, representing an intelligence operative willing to betray anyone for strategic advantage. He maintained connections with the Bridgeburners dating back to the initial Malazan conquest, with Kalam Mekhar claiming he owed him a personal debt from that era. Physically, he was a small man with sharp silver-capped teeth who carried a dagger at his belt, presenting an appearance befitting his shadowy profession as a spy and manipulator operating within occupied territory.
Messremb	A Soletaken capable of shapeshifting between human and animal forms. His animal form is a great brown bear as huge as a noble-born's carriage. In his human guise, he presents quite differently: an emaciated figure no taller than five feet, nearly hairless with a narrow face, prominent teeth, and small garnet eyes set within laugh lines. He shares a long history with Mappo Runt, having known him long ago when both lived in the pine forests of the Trell north of Nemil, suggesting he is an old, powerful being with deep roots in the world's mythology and geography.
Minala	Wife of Colonel Tras, commander of the Malazan garrison at Orbal on Seven Cities, originally from Quon. Sister of Selv, whose husband Keneb served at Orbal. Described as attractive and medium boned with iron streaked hair and startling grey eyes, and known as an exceptionally skilled rider who endured an abusive marriage.
Moby	A familiar of Mammot, a scholar, living in Mammot's study eating grapes and drinking out of the scholar's inkwells. Following his master's death, the creature demonstrated unusual loyalty by accompanying Crokus, Fiddler, and Kalam on their journey through Seven Cities, with his attachment to Fiddler in particular hinting at an intelligence and emotional capacity beyond typical familiars.
Nil	Wickan warlock and twin brother of Nether, affiliated with the Malaz 7th Army. Long unkempt black hair and a reedy voice, he sometimes carried a feather bedecked knobbed club. He served in Sormo Enath cadre as a boy and traveled to Hissar to support Coltaine.
Nether	Wickan warlock or witch and twin sister to Nil, affiliated with the Malaz 7th Army. Dark skin and eyes like black liquid, hair cut bristly short, and a high piping voice. One of the reborn Wickan warlocks, she carried knowledge and strength beyond her years while serving in Sormo Enath cadre as a child.
Nok	Admiral and Supreme Commander of the Imperial Malaz Navy, commanding from his flagship the Star of Unta. He was one of the last surviving members of Emperor Kellanved's original inner circle, distinguished as "the only admiral who didn't drown" among that legendary cadre. Renowned for his taciturn nature and cold demeanor earning him the epithet "cold iron," he presented as a quite old but well preserved man with weathered features, sporting distinctive white hair, thin snowy brows, and a white moustache and goatee, with a tall thin frame reflecting decades of service at sea.
Pearl	Mockra mage and Claw agent, tall and handsome with dark skin and a lean sharp featured face, green eyes, green silks, and rings of green hued gems. One quarter Tiste Andii. He wore a belt of throwing stars and a brace of throwing knives under his half cloak, and had once been Topper favored lieutenant.
Pella	Malazan soldier garrisoned at the Otataral mining camp Skullcup. A young man called the boy, with calluses ridging the index finger and thumb of his sword hand. He guarded Nearlight Gate and quoted Kellanved from Duiker Imperial Campaigns while on duty.
Ryllandaras	Soletaken and D'ivers known as the White Jackal, White Jackal of Winter, and Quon Curse. In man jackal form he is towering and powerful with sandy yellow fur fading to creamy white at throat and chest, dark streaks along the back, long limbs and amber claws, a long black muzzle, and dark carmine eyes.
Sawark	Captain and Malazan commander of the guard in the Otataral mining camp Skullcup, presiding from a hexagonal tower keep. Pale, thin, and wiry, with twisted cable like forearm muscles, an oiled beard, short black hair, watery green eyes, high cheekbones, and a wide mouth that rarely smiled.
Sha'ik	The title for the chosen one of the Whirlwind Goddess, also known as the "Hand of Dryjhna" and "Seeress of the Apocalypse." The original Sha'ik was a prophetess and leader of the Whirlwind rebellion in the Holy Desert Raraku. She was a small, dark-haired woman whose appearance reflected her harsh desert life.
Sormo E'nath|Sormo|E'nath	Reincarnation of the greatest Wickan warlock of the same name, reborn after his death at Unta and said to be about ten years old when he led Coltaine warlocks. Tall bow legged boy with dark eyes, a goat head cowl, and a reedy voice, bearing the aura and scent of an ancient warlock who had reached the Time of Iron.
T'amber	Aide and rumored lover of Adjunct Tavore Paran, quiet and not very talkative, described as beautiful and remote with unclear origins, her name tied to a tawny mane or amber colored eyes.
Tavore Paran|Tavore	Second child of house Paran, sister to Ganoes and Felisin.<br><br> <i>"Command does not come from consensus. I deliver the orders and my officers are to obey them. They should be relieved that is the case, for all responsibility lies with me and me alone. No-one else shall have to answer to the empress."</i>
Tene Baralta|Baralta	Commander of the Ehrlitan Red Blades, a military unit native to Seven Cities, who eventually rises to the rank of Fist within the Malazan Empire's 14th Army. Physically, he cuts an imposing figure—described as tall, broad, and dusk-skinned with a distinctive beard kept slick with oil, reflecting his vanity noted by fellow soldiers. Those who serve under him, like Lostara Yil, perceive him as somewhat self-serving: someone willing to take credit for every success while avoiding responsibility for failures, creating tension between his authoritative bearing and questionable judgment.
Toblakai	Escaped slave and fanatically loyal warrior of the Apocalypse in the Holy Desert Raraku, bodyguard to Sha'ik Elder alongside Leoman. A giant over seven feet tall with a wide muscled frame, flat broad face marked by shattered glass tattoos, a single long braid, and a cloak of bhederin hide over shell like armor.
